description: It's a special double date issue as the surviving members of the Six take a night on the town in that disturbing way that only they can do. It's dinner and a movie with bullets and bloodshed in an all-romance (with violence) issue you won't want to miss! Plus, what does Ragdoll dream about? Um, it's not for the squeamish.
name: Double Date; Ragdoll Dreams

description: An offbeat one-shot featuring STAR TREK's most unlikely alien race! Welcome to Serjilla IV, an abandoned world completely overrun by Tribbles: friendly, trilling balls of fur that eat constantly and, in the words of Dr. Leonard McCoy, 'reproduce at will.' When a human freighter, boarded by hostile Klingons, crash-lands on Serjilla, the Tribbles' quiet but lonely existence is shattered. It's a simple situation, really-three desperate humans, a squadron of angry Klingons, and a billion hungry Tribbles. What could possibly go wrong?

Discover the early years of Soulfire's heroine Grace as the all-new Soulfire: Shadow Magic mini-series reaches its grand conclusion! The war rages into its final act as the Sethoru and Rahtumi are interlocked in a battle spread across the land-with devastating losses on both sides. The wizard Azar's ultimate plan for genocide has reached a shocking pinnacle and his fate rests on one final step. Reyna is granted her wish to fight in the war, but the ensuing result is far worse than what she ever thought possible. And the two lovers, Grace and Kelsyn, painfully discover the price of re-entering the battle, and the repercussions of their decision will change their fate forever!
name: The Bounds of Eternity

description: Macking, body fluids, and bad words abound as Ubu Bubu crashes into its fourth and final issue as events spiral dramatically out of control. It's not enough that Ubu Bubu has to control the daemons of Pestilence, Perversion, and the newly-spewed Gluttony as they try to cause dirty havoc on Earth, but also defend himself against the most emo of Satans who has come to drag Lord Bubu back to Hell! Not to mention God's heavies, the Nephilim, trying to have a bit of the ruckus as the Apocalypse finally kicks in and Earth becomes a winner-take-all human harvest. Everyone's out for Ubu Bubu's blood, and it can only end brutally!
name: Ubu Bubu Must Die

description: 2009meets 2099? Future history has been shattered by events in the present! If you think you know the heroes and villains from Marvels dark future, writer Brian Reed (SECRET INVASION: CAPTAIN MARVEL) and artist Eric Battle (Batman) say its time to think again! Get ready for the re-imagined 2099 versions of Spider-Man, Ghost Rider, the X-Men and more! Plus 8 pages of Director's Cut Extras!
name: Timestorm, Part 1

Overview

The Soul Market is now open for business... In a remote country estate in upstate New York, a unique emporium hasset up business: The Soul Market. On display, the imprisoned souls of mortals held inside portraits, sculptures, and photographs ... all to be auctioned off to the highest bidder. The mastermind behind this bizarre enterprise is the notorious Faerie called Goodfellow. But what does he hope to gain from this auction of souls? Lady Kildare intends to find out.

description: Artist Pete Woods returns for a story years in the making - a day in the life of Maxine Manchester! Maxine finds that she's able to make a very unique difference in post-apocalyptic Los Angeles. And in part 1 of a special backup, the critically acclaimed Puncture creative team of Russell Utley and Ben Oliver reunite for a dark look at the WildCats' enemy, Defile!
name: Computer Love

description: 'LIAR'S POKER,' PART 1-The latest addition to Marvel's red-hot Noir line offers a unique spin on the Man Without Fear! Prohibition-era Hell's Kitchen is Kingpin territory, and until now, his only problem has been the masked vigilante known as Daredevil. When gangster Orville Halloran arrives on the scene, fresh from a stretch in Sing Sing and eager to stretch his wings, Hell's about to get hotter. For P.I. Foggy Nelson and his loyal assistant Matt Murdock, it all starts when a desperate woman comes to their office with an irresistible story about her and Halloran. To Foggy, she's a client -- to Murdock, she's enough to make Halloran Daredevil's next target. But Murdock is about to find out that half-truths are poison truths, and that the Kitchen is full of history that will put him on a collision course with both the old Kingpin and the man who wants to replace him.
name: Liar's Poker

description: How much would people hate you if you destroyed their heroes? It's all-out war as the new Captain Action throws down with the Public Protectors! The 'people's heroes' aren't what they claim to be, but no one knows that but Cap! And there isn't much time, as his powers begin to fail him, and he has no one he can count on - or so he thinks! Meanwhile, Crescent is about to eliminate someone from the past, but who can get the drop on the ultimate infiltrator? Be here as time catches up with Captain Action! Plus, the first-ever story of Lady Action!
name: For The Public Good; BBQ; The Waxwork

description: Doktor Sleepless, by all accounts of the Heavenside media, is an all-powerful and angry god who can turn off the electricity at will, has brought angels to earth, and is remaking the city in his own image. But as each new story whips the rumors of the mad Doktor to terrifying proportions, the more frightening truth is that he may be beginning to believe his own press! Warren Ellis' satirical-political science fiction novel continues its on-going run! The issue is available with a regular cover by series artist Ivan Rodriguez, or wraparound cover by Raulo Caceres, and also a rare Future Warning Sign cover.
name: Salvage Messiah

Debuting as both enemy and ally of the Werewolf by Night, Moon Knight's three personalities equaled one eerie adventure after another by Moench, Miller and more! Earning enemies like the brutal Bushman and the macabre Morpheus early in his career, Moon Knight also teamed up with Spider-Man, the Thing, and others against well-known and forgotten villains alike! Spun by Cyclone! Caught by Crossfire! Plus: an early fight with the Purple Man alongside Luke Cage! Featuring Topaz from WITCHES and the original White Tiger!

description:
The place? Japan. The time? 150 years in the future. The situation?The Japanese goverment has perfected the art of artificial intelligence and succeeded in manufacturing a robotic army.

When a young boy named Jimmu stumbles onto some foul play an intense chain of events is set into motion, including the activation of N.I.O., a robotic warrior programmed to protect Jimmu at all costs. But what happens when N.I.O.'s memory and programming are corrupted by an outside source - the engrams of a human female accidentally downloaded into the N.I.O. programming? Will N.I.O. have a more human and humane agenda than the human does?
Jimmu's parents are dead and he's next on Kembei's hit list! With N.I.O. Prime the only thing that stands between him and a robotic army, will Corbin and Jimmu be able to trust this rogue unit?
N.I.O. Prime, Corbin and Jimmu take the fight into the heart of Project: N.I.O.... and right straight into Director Kembei's clutches!
Deep in the heart of Director Kembei's sanctum N.I.O. Prime will face her ultimate nemesis, the lethal artificial intelligence known only as Shuten Doji.

For seventy years, Galloway & Galloway has dominated the pharmaceutical field. From band aids to cough syrup, G&G made life easier for all of us. Then they decided to make life itself. In the early '80s, G&G created the next step in evolution -- a race of genetically engineered superhumans, each bred with specifically endowed enhanced abilities. But the company -- and the G&G employees who volunteered to be the test subject's parents -- never took into account one very important thing -- puberty! XL! BLUR! CALAMITY! REBOUND! They live the life most kids would love to have...and they'd be more than happy to trade with you!

Variants exist:

- Variant cover (pic 2)

- Retailer Review Copy

What if you could go back in time and fix a mistake you made? Would you? Strange energy readings are discovered in a remote region of Asia. XL will soon find out when G&G decides to investigate by sending the Troublemakers on their first field mission. Madness ensues when XL, Blur and Rebound accidentally release the insanity that is Crunchtime! Can the kids stop the temporal displacing wacko as he traverses wildly throughout time? Will XL fix what she did wrong on her first day of school?

Jane has a problem. Her powers could destroy the world, and she can't control them. Why? How come all of the other Troublemakers can control their biofields and she can't? This is the story of Calamity Jane. It's the story of a little girl trying to graduate from the school of hard knocks. It's a story that will make you cry, and make you smile.

What would you do if you saw your mother kissing another man? Blur must answer this question when his voyeuristic tendencies backfire on him and he catches his own mom starting an affair with another man at G&G. How does he get his father to pay attention to his mother's needs? How does he get his mom to stop? Can he prevent his parents from heading to divorce court? When Blur and his parents are all sent to fix an isolated G&G satellite relay station, all the poop hits the fan!
It's time for a little "Hero Worship" as Ninjak guest-stars! A riot breaks out at Menlo Park Mall, Rebound kicks butt and we introduce the mayhem of...The Bellicose Brothers!

XL and Rebound go where no Troublemaker has gone before -- into outer space! NASA needs G&G's help to fix a communication satellite which is suffering orbital decay. But what starts out as an incredible adventure turns into a shocking -- and deadly -- encounter with an alien life form very familiar to old-time Valiant readers!

There's a new teen team in town and they're looking to kick some Troublemaker butt! It's the dynamically dangerous debut of the Rabble Rousers! But where did they come from? And how does their existence tie in to Galloway & Galloway?

One of the group, Jane, has a mother who runs her own scientific facility, filled with super-powered teens as well. The problem is, Jane's mom has no sense of morality.

Rabble Rousers part deux! Katherine Desmond makes her move to take control of the Troublemakers. Jane must make a fateful decision between her mom or her dad. Parker goes to summer school. And Christine goes to the beach with a boy! Whew, lots of cool stuff!

The group fights a rival's super-powered team. All headed by the mother of one of their own.

XL is always better at anything then anyone near her. This is her power. But has this taken away her free will? When she's with someone attracted to her, does this mean her attraction to him goes even farther?
The group loses one of their own.

XL is sent to a science-research facility in Waco to investigate a comatose patient with extraordinary power. She becomes seduced by the strength of his will and abilities. Can she control excelling such a forceful violent person? How does she react to meeting a Harbinger now that she has learned she's not pregnant-she CAN'T get pregnant-EVER-because SHE'S NOT EVEN HUMAN???
Final Issue!

An armored Nazi soldier has been spotted in France, immune to artillery and unstoppable. Rumor has it that Germany is withing days of launching an atomic bomb. What do you do? Assemble the first team of superbeings to stop this threat to the entire planet. That's what! Enter the world of 1944 with Warmaster, Bravado, Nemesis, Jack Rapid and Doctor Tomorrow, and witness their battle against the Nazi incarnation of X-O Manowar!

Despite being called Vol 3 # 10 this is really the first issue of Jerry Drummer.

Before number one comics became the sought after things they are now comics with higher numbers were thought more valued by publishers thinking that customers seeing that the book, among all its rivals on the stand at that time, had been around for a while would think that it was worthwhile.

Charlton had done this with a number of other publications, Jerry Drummer however is unusual in that not only did they call the first issue # 10, they also marked as being Vol 3 indicating that this was the 34th outing for the Boy Hero of the Revolution, if that was the idea it did not work as Jerry only made it in this and two more issues.

He at least has the distention of having the second longest run of a comic book character set during the American Revolution after the far more successful Tomahawk at DC.
name: Jerry Drummer: Boy Hero of the Revolutionary War

description: Despite the numbering on the cover this isreally Jerry Drummer # 2
In fact this is the third and last Jerry Drummer
